articles.title: Gas price spike underscores Europe's vulnerability to global energy shocks - Financial Times
articles.description: Rapid reduction in flows from Russia has left continent competing with Asia for liquefied natural gas supplies
articles.content: This weeks violent surge in European gas prices underscores how the regions success in weaning itself off Russian energy has left it more vulnerable to the ebb and flow of volatile global energy mark… [+3839 chars]
